{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016UY4kTRSP2NkzXgUr9gLHe","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now let me compile my comprehensive findings:\n\n## Summary\n\nI've conducted a thorough search of the codebase and found all web UI files related to SSE logs display. Here are the complete findings:\n\n### **Go Handler Files**\n\n1. **/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go** - Main HTTP request handler\n   - Line 139: Registers `GET /api/runs/{id}/stream` endpoint mapped to `handleAPIStream`\n   - Lines 805-871: `handleAPIStream()` function that:\n     - Sets `Content-Type: text/event-stream` header\n     - Sets SSE-related headers (`Cache-Control: no-cache`, `Connection: keep-alive`, `X-Accel-Buffering: no`)\n     - Streams from full.log for completed runs (lines 832-838)\n     - Subscribes to live broadcaster for active runs (lines 841-870)\n     - Sends JSON-encoded log lines as SSE `data:` events\n     - Sends `event: done` message when stream completes\n   - Lines 876-898: `streamFullLog()` helper that reads archived full.log and flushes lines\n   - Lines 904-914: `parseLLMLogLine()` parses Claude streaming JSON\n   - Lines 917-931: `parseFullLogLine()` parses log format `[timestamp] [type] content`\n\n2. **/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler_stream_test.go** - SSE endpoint tests\n   - Line 34: `TestSSE_CompletedRun_ServesFullLog` - tests full.log streaming\n   - Line 90: `TestSSE_ActiveRun_StreamsLive` - tests live broadcaster streaming\n   - Line 156: `TestSSE_RunNotFound` - tests 404 handling\n   - Line 166: `TestSSE_NoBroadcaster_ActiveRun` - tests 503 when broadcaster unavailable\n   - Lines 188-236: `TestParseFullLogLine` - tests log parsing\n   - Lines 238-256: `TestSSE_CompletedRun_NoFullLog` - tests handling missing log file\n\n### **HTML Templates**\n\n1. **/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html** - Run details page\n   - Lines 101-105: Log viewer section with live status badge\n   - Lines 108-352: Embedded JavaScript that:\n     - Lines 141-162: Creates `EventSource` connection to `/api/runs/{runID}/stream`\n     - Parses incoming SSE `data:` events as JSON\n     - Appends parsed log lines to DOM with timestamp/type/content\n     - Listens for `done` event to mark log as complete\n     - Implements auto-scroll tracking based on scroll position (lines 120-124)\n     - Handles errors and closes connection on error\n\n2. **/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/layout.html** - Base template wrapper\n   - Minimal markup; contains navbar and content/scripts blocks\n\n3. **/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/runs.html** - Runs list page\n   - Polling-based updates (no SSE), fetches `/api/runs` every 3 seconds\n\n4. **/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/projects.html** - Projects overview page\n   - No SSE or streaming\n\n5. **/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html** - Project details page\n   - No SSE or streaming (workflow visualization only)\n\n### **CSS Styling**\n\n**/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css** - Styling for logs\n   - Lines 387-410: `.log-viewer` and `.log-line` classes\n   - `.log-viewer`: 600px max-height, auto-overflow, monospace font\n   - `.log-type-status`: Blue text for status messages\n   - `.log-type-llm`: Green text for LLM messages\n   - `.log-type-script`: Default text for script output\n\n### **Supporting Package**\n\n**/workspace/internal/logstream/broadcaster.go** - Live log fan-out mechanism\n   - `LogLine` struct (lines 8-13): timestamp, type (status/script/llm), content, step_name\n   - `Broadcaster` struct: Manages subscriptions for active runs\n   - `Subscribe()`: Registers new subscriber, returns channel receiving LogLines\n   - `Publish()`: Sends log line to all subscribers (non-blocking, drops if slow)\n   - `Finish()`: Marks run complete, closes all subscriber channels\n   - 256-item buffer per subscriber (line 64)\n\n### **Key Architecture Points**\n\n1. **Dual Stream Mode**:\n   - Completed runs: Reads from disk archive (`.cloche/{runID}/output/full.log`)\n   - Active runs: Subscribes to in-memory broadcaster fed by agent\n\n2. **Event Format**:\n   - SSE line format: `data: {JSON}` where JSON is `{timestamp, type, content, step_name?}`\n   - Terminal event: `event: done\\ndata: {state}\\n\\n`\n\n3. **Client-Side Behavior**:\n   - Uses standard `EventSource` API (no polyfills needed)\n   - Auto-scroll enabled when viewport at bottom (within 40px threshold)\n   - Disables auto-scroll when user manually scrolls up\n   - Re-enables when scrolled back to bottom\n\n4. **Log Parsing**:\n   - Full format: `[2026-03-03T10:15:00Z] [status] step_started: build`\n   - Fallback: Unstructured lines get type \"script\" with current timestamp\n   - LLM lines: Claude JSON stream decoded to human text\n\nAll files are located in `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/` for handlers/templates/styles and `/workspace/internal/logstream/` for the broadcaster infrastructure."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a695f5d1861d3981c (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 56872\ntool_uses: 25\nduration_ms: 38754</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b4591c00-1384-4a12-a964-ae35a19bcedb","uuid":"640a16b5-1cb7-4786-b62f-a645e406c5d0","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Find all web UI files related to SSE logs display. Look for HTML templates, JavaScript files, and Go handlers that serve the web UI for log streaming. Search for patterns like \"SSE\", \"EventSource\", \"logs\", \"scroll\", \"text/event-stream\" in the codebase. Be very thorough - check all file types including .html, .js, .go, .tmpl, .css files.","agentId":"a695f5d1861d3981c","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now let me compile my comprehensive findings:\n\n## Summary\n\nI've conducted a thorough search of the codebase and found all web UI files related to SSE logs display. Here are 