{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01HhdjHt6a5fqTSED1GD69ap","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I understand the issue. The current code has the right idea with `autoScroll` tracking, but it's not robust enough. Each individual `appendLogLine` call triggers a DOM append and potential scroll, which can cause jitter during rapid SSE bursts. The fix is to batch DOM updates using `requestAnimationFrame` and a `DocumentFragment`, and to explicitly save/restore scroll position when not auto-scrolling.\n\nLet me also check for any related tests."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1067,"cache_read_input_tokens":21562,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1067},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b4591c00-1384-4a12-a964-ae35a19bcedb","uuid":"34088003-7c9f-47f5-84bd-fe4d90d5a80a"}
